qpasswd (0.5-0njl9.0) stretch-backports; urgency=medium

  * Update for modern packaging standards (last changed for Debian 3.1 Sarge):
    - source format now "3.0 (quilt)"
    - update copyright to DEP-5
    - convert debian/rules to use dh
    - override "make": export dh environment; suppress stripping.
      Let Debian Build System choose the right build arch.
    - install into /bin not /command, it's the 21st century and FHS exists.
      Use /bin since that's where the old package symlinked things.
  * Update Makefile
    - fix build and exec path for "make test".
    - remove explicit compile options, use Debian environment.
    - make multicheckpw and the rest world-executable.

 -- Nick Leverton <nick@leverton.org>  Wed, 19 Apr 2023 23:55:04 +0100

